The paper discusses the generalization and optimization performance of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper also involves theoretical analysis of optimization algorithms, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
